# Zealthy — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values. `.env` is git-ignored.

# ─── Postgres connection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any Postgres locally; Neon in production.
#
# Local: a single connection string is all you need.
#   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/zealthy?schema=public"
#
# Neon (production): the app runs its runtime queries over the POOLED connection
# (serverless-friendly), while Prisma migrations must run over the DIRECT
# (unpooled) connection — PgBouncer's transaction pooling doesn't support the
# session-level advisory locks `prisma migrate` uses.
#   • Runtime  →  the pooled string      (host like ...-pooler.neon.tech)
#   • Migrate  →  the unpooled string    (host WITHOUT `-pooler`)
#
# When Neon is provisioned via the Vercel Marketplace integration, Vercel injects
# these automatically into the deployment (no manual copy needed):
#   DATABASE_URL           → pooled       (used by the app at runtime)
#   DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED  → direct       (used for `npm run db:deploy` / seeding)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/zealthy?schema=public"

# ─── Auth.js (NextAuth v5) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Session-signing secret. Generate one with:
#   npx auth secret        (or)        openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET="replace-with-a-generated-secret"
